window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Shortlisted for the Costa Best Novel Award 2018<br> Longlisted for the Man Booker Prize 2018</b></p> <p>Random House presents the audiobook edition of <i>From a Low and Quiet Sea</i> by Donal Ryan, read by Stephen Hogan, Gerry O'Brien and Ramon Tikaram.</p> <p>Farouk’s country has been torn apart by war.</p> <p>Lampy’s heart has been laid waste by Chloe.</p> <p>John’s past torments him as he nears his end.</p> <p>The refugee. The dreamer. The penitent. From war-torn Syria to small-town Ireland, three men, scarred by all they have loved and lost, are searching for some version of home. Each is drawn towards a powerful reckoning, one that will bring them together in the most unexpected of ways.</p>"; 
